In order for the system manager to allocate resources, four conditions must be met. First, the system manager must have some additional resources to allocate. Second, the system manager must be convinced that there is a problem that needs to be solved. Third, the system manager must be convinced that this is the most important problem to be solved. Fourth, the system manager must be convinced that allocating his scarce resource will actually solve the problem. The human factors manager must address these concerns.